2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): RNN models are widely used in computer vision tasks such as activity recognition, which is the focus of the evaluation in this paper. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language): RNN models are also widely used in natural language processing tasks, which fall under this sub-category. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses optimizations for executing neural network models on mobile devices, which falls under this sub-category. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses GPU offloading specifically for mobile GPUs, which falls under this sub-category.
